      <profileDesc>
         <abstract>
            <p>Collection of medical prescriptions in a mixture of Gǝʾǝz and Amharic, which is reported to originate from Jerusalem, attested in
               <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient828">London, British Library, BL Oriental 828</ref>. It differs from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7529Madhanit">Maṣḥafa Madḫanit</ref> and 
               <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7530MashafaMad">Maṣḥafa Madḫanit</ref>.</p>
         </abstract>
         <langUsage>
            <language ident="en">English</language>
            <language ident="am">Amharic</language>
            <language ident="gez">Gǝʾǝz</language>
         </langUsage>
